<br>
It sortuf bugged me that there is like 30 something combines (I think, memory is fuzzy) and I was only getting to 8, especially since the first combines are supposed to be 120ish trivals.....Maybe others have/will have better luck, but having to redo the quest basically from scratch over and over and over is not my idea of fun.  I just stopped to take a breather, and got lucky and got my epic in that time.  Don't plan to do this quest now, maybe someday later on for fun.<br>
<br>
I should have got to 200 on smithing I guess (hardest part of combines is supposed to be trival in 170's, it used to be like 220 but was lowered), but I had burnt a lot of money as it was and it was only getting more expensive.  Also my last attempt to raise smithing really was no fun at all (pre-tradeskill patch), it took over 400 combines to get 1 skill point...that of course required lots of time gathering pelts to make leather padding to do it the cheaper route other then ornate chain.  Now I think plate is trival much lower, so it would be more expensive.<br>
<br>
Don't want to sound like a bummer about all this, others have much better luck, but just know what your up against is all I am saying.  If all else fails there are other weapons of similar nature that are easier to obtain.<br>
<br>
